distStmt.distrbtr: United States Department of Commerce. Bureau of the Census. Research Data Center

stdyInfo.abstract: The Employment History File (EHF) provides a full time-series of earnings at all within-state jobs for all quarters covered by the LEHD system and provided by the state. It also provides activity calendars at a job, firm, and sub-firm reporting unit level. The EHF contains no Federal Tax Information (FTI).

useStmt.confDec: To obtain this dataset, the user must complete the RDC application process, and be approved for use of this dataset.
useStmt.restrctn: MOU between Census Bureau and individual state agencies. Protected under Title 13
useStmt.conditions: Users must (I) successfully apply for RDC access (ii) pass review by agencies (iii) pass security clearance
useStmt.disclaimer: No edits have been applied to these data. Under-reporting, data loss, etc. may affect diverse states and quarters. The data documentation has an up-to-date list of such data issues. The LEHD Program suggests users use Bayesian multiple imputation models to address such issues.

dimensns.recNumTot: 8 billion records in 8 files per state. Record counts per state vary.
